# Function Comments and Tests

- Add a clear, detailed docstring/comment for every function you create or edit.
- For backend Python:
  - Add a function docstring describing inputs, behavior, and return value.
  - Add inline comments ahead of non-obvious logic blocks (ranking, filtering, joins, gates).
- For frontend TypeScript/React:
  - Add JSDoc-style comments for exported functions/components/hooks.
  - Add short comments for important formatting or state-management helpers.
- Keep comments accurate and maintain them when code behavior changes.
- Every new feature/fix must include automated tests:
  - Add or update backend tests for new endpoints/jobs/logic.
  - Run the full backend test suite before finishing.
  - Run frontend build/typecheck when frontend code changes.

